<section class="lp-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="eyebrow">the approach</div>
      <h2>we don't need your bank to help you save money.</h2>
      <p>the fintech playbook is the same everywhere: ask for read-only access to your bank, categorise your spending, and sell you some version of "we'll optimise it." we think that model is fundamentally broken — for trust and for results.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="not-grid" style="margin-top:0;">
      <div class="not-card">
        <div class="not-mark">✕</div>
        <h3>no open banking</h3>
        <p>we never connect to your financial accounts. no read-only access, no "just this once" permissions, no api tokens stored on a server somewhere. your bank data stays with your bank.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-card">
        <div class="not-mark">✕</div>
        <h3>no affiliate incentives</h3>
        <p>we don't get paid when you switch providers. no kickbacks, no sponsored recommendations, no "best deals" that are best for us, not you. our verdicts are unconflicted.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-card">
        <div class="not-mark">✕</div>
        <h3>no data mining</h3>
        <p>we don't sell data, train models on your information, or package it up for advertisers. the documents you send us are used for exactly one purpose: extracting your renewal details.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</div>

